description:
This is the 1978 BBC mini series &quot;The Voyage of Charles Darwin&quot; 
about the life and theories of Darwin. It consists of seven 1-hour 
episodes. 

It was directed by Martyn Friend, produced by Christoper Ralling, 
written by Robert Raid, and stars Malcom Stoddard as Darwin. See &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0216517/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0216517/&lt;/a&gt;

It comes to you via TV, VHS and YouTube, so the quality is limited. 

Video codec: XVID (MPEG-4 ASP, plays fine with VLC or ffdshow)
Audio codec: MPGA (MP2)

You can also watch the show in 10-minute segments on YouTube or in 
1-hour segments on Veoh.
